    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Jim to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin <date value="1916-09-12">Sept 12th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-09-12">Sept 12th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Marcelle:</salute>
            </opener>
            
            <p>
            There is
            nothing new with me
            except that I’m getting
            mighty sick of this
            place with the prayers
            and music of soup
            eating etc.  Yet the
            Major tells me I’m in
            for ten days more.
    
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            The big offensive is coming
            off soon and I’m afraid 
            I’ll miss that.  Well, any
            way the war looks favorable
            and that’s cheering.
            </p><p>
            I guess you’ve been
            working hard after all
            this fighting but you’ll 
            have more in the near
            future I’m afraid.
            </p><p>
            This morning 2,000
            motor lorries passed thru [sic]
            here going north.
            
            <pb n="[p.3]"/>
            
            As you have read 
            and appreciated Spoon
            River I know you
            will enjoy the inclosed [sic].
            Both sides.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>My best to you</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            Hopital Mixte<lb/>
            Vitry le Francois<lb/>
            Marne
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
            <!-- [With this letter is an envelope addressed to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin, 148 Bis Rue de Longchamp, XVI, Paris.] -->
            
            </div1>
        </body>
